          "text": "<teammate-message teammate_id=\"carddav-reviewer\" color=\"green\" summary=\"CardDAV test quality review complete\">\n## Task #2: CardDAV Test Quality & RFC Compliance Review\n\nI reviewed all three test files against their source files and the RFC 6352 specification. Here are my findings organized by test file.\n\n---\n\n### 1. ecard-carddav-test.el (~2500 lines, ~80+ tests)\n\n**GOOD: Authentication coverage is thorough**\n- Tests basic auth, bearer token, OAuth2 creation, header generation, expiration, refresh, and validation edge cases (lines 87-981)\n- Properly tests auth-source integration with mock (lines 985-1020)\n- Tests auth function resolution in server creation (lines 1038-1053, 1774-1791)\n\n**GOOD: Core protocol operations are well-tested**\n- Discovery chain (principal → addressbook-home → addressbooks) is tested individually and end-to-end (lines 149-192, 621-681)\n- PUT/GET/DELETE with ETag validation covers happy path and conflicts (lines 194-343)\n- Multiget batch retrieval tested with multiple resources, empty list, absolute URLs, parse errors (lines 1179-1942)\n- Retry logic for 5xx with exponential backoff tested (lines 1843-1875)\n\n**GOOD: RFC 6352 compliance areas tested**\n- sync-collection REPORT body generation and handling (lines 1493-1504, 2055-2127)\n- addressbook-multiget REPORT body (lines 1078-1087, 1508-1516)\n- PROPFIND body generation with proper namespaces (lines 1067-1076)\n- ETag-based concurrency control (lines 256-313)\n- Sync-token incremental sync (lines 406-443, 2055-2093)\n- CTag-based change detection (lines 1558-1587, 1946-2013)\n\n**GOOD: Mock server internals are independently validated**\n- XML parsing, escaping, response construction, PROPFIND at various depths (lines 1097-1175, 2129-2268)\n- Edge cases: invalid vCard PUT, missing addressbook paths, nonexistent resource PROPFIND (lines 2161-2214)\n\n**GOOD: URL resolution tested**\n- Absolute URL, absolute path, and relative path resolution (lines 1627-1646)\n- Principal and addressbook-home URL extraction with both relative and absolute hrefs (lines 2311-2393)\n\n**GOOD: vCard 3.0 compatibility and line-ending handling**\n- Tests version 3.0 serialization path and LF line ending conversion (lines 1722-1770)\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Conflict resolution tests create sync objects without addressbook**\n- Lines 1229-1379: Tests like `ecard-carddav-test-sync-conflict-server-wins` create `ecard-carddav-sync` directly without `ecard-carddav-sync-create`, bypassing validation. This works because the conflict resolution function only reads the `:strategy` slot, but it's fragile if the constructor ever adds validation logic.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Some tests don't verify complete state**\n- `ecard-carddav-test-sync-collection-deleted-resources` (line 2097): Only checks `(listp result)` after deletion but doesn't verify the deleted path appears in `:deleted` or that the local cache was cleaned. The test exercises the code path but doesn't fully assert correct behavior.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Mock state leakage potential**\n- The `ecard-carddav-test--mock-server` and `ecard-carddav-test--temp-dir` module-level variables could leak between tests if `unwind-protect` teardown is missed. All tests do use unwind-protect properly, but a single missed teardown could cascade failures.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Add test for .well-known/carddav redirect**\n- RFC 6352 Section 11 specifies service discovery via `.well-known/carddav`. The mock server doesn't appear to test this redirect path, which is important for real-world compatibility.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Test Content-Type header in PUT requests**\n- RFC 6352 requires `text/vcard` content type. The tests verify data correctness but don't explicitly assert the Content-Type header sent in PUT requests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. ecard-carddav-map-test.el (~1530 lines, ~45+ tests)\n\n**GOOD: Comprehensive functional coverage**\n- Empty addressbook, no-modifications, all-modifications, partial-modifications, skip, delete (lines 103-247)\n- Mixed operations combining modify/delete/skip in single pass (lines 546-574)\n- Idempotency: running same transformation twice yields zero second modifications (lines 578-608)\n\n**GOOD: Change detection is properly validated**\n- `ecard-carddav-map-test-false-modification-claim` (line 251): Tests that returning `t` without actual vCard change is detected as \"no change\" — this is a critical correctness test for the before/after serialization comparison.\n- `ecard-carddav-map-test-actual-modification-detected` (line 269): Confirms real changes are detected.\n\n**GOOD: Error handling coverage is excellent**\n- Transformation errors (lines 288-313, 1340-1357)\n- ETag conflicts with all strategies: skip, force, retry-once (lines 315-415)\n- Serialization errors during change detection (lines 1307-1336)\n- Generic update/delete errors (lines 1361-1504)\n- Multiget fallback with individual fetch failures (lines 1253-1303)\n- Force/retry failure paths when re-fetch also fails (lines 1387-1475)\n\n**GOOD: Progress reporting validated**\n- Progress callbacks tested for correct invocation frequency and monotonic progress counts (lines 419-474)\n\n**GOOD: Real-world usage patterns tested**\n- Adding UIDs to contacts missing them (lines 644-680)\n- Phone number normalization (lines 682-719)\n- Bulk duplicate deletion (lines 721-769) — though this doesn't use `ecard-carddav-map-resources` directly, it tests the manual workflow\n\n**GOOD: Stats helper unit tests**\n- `make-stats` defaults and keyword args (lines 773-789)\n- `update-stats` with copy semantics and error accumulation (lines 791-811)\n\n**ISSUE (moderate): `ecard-carddav-map-test-bulk-delete-duplicates` doesn't use the map API**\n- Line 721: This test bypasses `ecard-carddav-map-resources` and manually iterates/deletes. It tests the underlying CardDAV primitives but not the map module's delete functionality with duplicate detection. This is more of an integration test for the primitives than a map module test.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Duplicate test**\n- `ecard-carddav-map-test-mock-propfind-home-depth1-lists-addressbooks` (line 1227) and `ecard-carddav-map-test-mock-propfind-home-depth1` (line 1239) appear identical — same setup, same assertions, same behavior.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Filter function regex could match unintended paths**\n- Line 538: `(string-match \"contact[1-5]\\\\.vcf$\" path)` — the character class `[1-5]` would also match \"contact15.vcf\" in the middle. Works correctly in the test since there are only 10 contacts, but the pattern is slightly misleading.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Test batch-size boundary conditions**\n- Test with batch-size=1 (forces individual processing) and batch-size larger than total contacts. The current tests use batch-size=5 with 20 items, which is good, but edge cases are missing.\n\n---\n\n### 3. ecard-sync-test.el (~1355 lines, ~50+ tests)\n\n**GOOD: Org-to-ecard conversion thoroughly tested**\n- Full property mapping including FN, N, EMAIL, TEL, ADR, ORG, NOTE, BDAY, GEO, CATEGORIES, UID (lines 75-123)\n- Minimal properties (lines 125-149)\n- Edge cases: structured vs plain address, no-org-mode error, multiple email addresses (lines 534-568)\n\n**GOOD: Ecard-to-org update tested bidirectionally**\n- Basic update preserving ID (lines 153-178)\n- ID adoption from server (lines 180-194)\n- GEO formatting, categories as tags, note as body text (lines 587-656)\n- Address as list and string, ORG as list and string (lines 628-656)\n- Legacy NOTE property removal (lines 878-900)\n\n**GOOD: Merge logic properly exercises timestamp-based direction**\n- `ecard-sync-test-determine-prefer-local-server-newer` (line 272): Server REV > SYNCED → prefer server\n- `ecard-sync-test-determine-prefer-local-server-older` (line 281): Server REV < SYNCED → prefer local\n- Equal timestamps (line 660), no REV (line 290), no SYNCED (line 264)\n\n**GOOD: Full sync workflow tested end-to-end with mock server**\n- New contact creation (lines 1065-1090)\n- Existing contact merge by UID (lines 1092-1130)\n- Contact found by FN with UID adoption (lines 1132-1168)\n- No org ID with FN match (lines 1170-1205) and no match (lines 1207-1232)\n- Sync-all-entries with multiple headings (lines 1236-1271) and error handling (lines 1273-1312)\n- Timestamp-based merge direction integration (lines 1316-1352)\n\n**GOOD: UTF-********byte fix thoroughly tested**\n- ASCII body, multibyte body, no body, empty body cases (lines 327-525, 797-817)\n- Verifies unibyte result and byte preservation\n\n**GOOD: Helper functions unit tested**\n- Name splitting (2, 3, 4 parts, single name, whitespace) (lines 44-704)\n- Location parsing/formatting including negative coords and nil (lines 60-473)\n- Empty value detection, slot empty detection (lines 412-445)\n- Clean string with invisible Unicode characters (lines 449-458)\n- Debug logging on/off, cache clearing (lines 355-384)\n- Server configuration normalization (lines 388-408)\n\n**GOOD: Resource discovery functions tested**\n- `ensure-resources` (fetch, empty, cached paths) (lines 904-953)\n- `find-resource-by-uid` (found, not found) (lines 955-990)\n- `find-resource-by-fn` (found, not found, multiple matches with completing-read mock) (lines 994-1061)\n\n**ISSUE (moderate): Round-trip test is weak**\n- `ecard-sync-test-round-trip` (line 304): Only checks FN and EMAIL match after org→ecard→org→ecard. Should verify more properties (TEL, ADR, ORG, GEO, CATEGORIES, NOTE) to ensure the round trip is complete.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Merge tests don't verify all properties**\n- `ecard-sync-test-merge-prefer-local` (line 198) and `ecard-sync-test-merge-prefer-server` (line 221) only check email and tel. The merge function handles many more slots; testing a few more would increase confidence.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Mock completing-read in FN test is simplistic**\n- `ecard-sync-test-find-resource-by-fn-multiple-matches` (line 1033): The mock `completing-read` just returns `(car choices)`, which doesn't validate that the choices presented are correct or properly formatted.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Test address book selection with ecard-sync-addressbook-name**\n- `ecard-sync-test-get-addressbook-by-name` exists but only tests the happy path. Consider testing with multiple addressbooks to verify the correct one is selected.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Test sync with pre-existing SYNCED timestamp**\n- The timestamp merge direction tests (`determine-prefer-local-*`) are unit tests. An integration test showing that a contact with an existing SYNCED timestamp correctly picks the right merge direction during `ecard-sync-entry` would strengthen confidence.\n\n---\n\n### Overall Assessment\n\nThe test suite is **high quality** overall:\n- **Strong points**: Excellent error path coverage, proper test isolation with setup/teardown, meaningful assertions (not just \"did it run\"), good mock server that simulates real protocol behavior\n- **RFC compliance**: The tests cover the key RFC 6352 requirements (PROPFIND, REPORT types, ETag concurrency, sync-token, multiget). The mock server implements enough of the protocol to validate real interactions.\n- **Coverage breadth**: All major code paths in the source files appear to be exercised\n- **No critical issues found**: All assertions appear correct, tests are well-isolated, mock state is properly cleaned up\n\nThe moderate issues (weak round-trip test, manual delete in map test) are worth addressing but don't indicate incorrect behavior. The minor issues are mostly about test hygiene and could be addressed opportunistically.\n\n</teammate-message>",
