          "text": "<teammate-message teammate_id=\"carddav-reviewer\" color=\"green\">\n{\"type\":\"idle_notification\",\"from\":\"carddav-reviewer\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-15T17:51:41.503Z\",\"idleReason\":\"available\"}\n</teammate-message>\n\n<teammate-message teammate_id=\"display-reviewer\" color=\"yellow\" summary=\"Display & widget test review complete with findings\">\n## Test Quality Review Complete: Display & Widget Modules\n\n### Overview\n- **ecard-display-test.el**: ~85 tests, 2578 lines\n- **ecard-widget-test.el**: ~63 tests, 968 lines\n\n### Critical Findings\n\n**1. Silent `when` guards (CRITICAL - both files)**\nThe most significant issue across both files. At least 12+ tests use this pattern:\n```elisp\n(let ((fn-widget (cdr (assq 'fn ecard-widget--widgets))))\n  (when fn-widget\n    (widget-value-set fn-widget \"New Name\")))\n```\nIf widget creation regresses and stops producing the expected keys, these tests pass vacuously - they never modify anything but still \"pass\". Found at widget-test lines: 130, 151-155, 177, 197, 221-225, 248-250, 264, 287-289, 380-382, 410-412, 424, 506-508, 898. And display-test lines: 1124-1126, 1146-1153, 1190-1192.\n\n**Fix**: Replace `when` with `(should fn-widget)` + unconditional call.\n\n**2. Inverted assertion pattern in display test** (line 336)\n`ecard-display-test-contact-detail-nil-ecard` uses `(should (condition-case _err (progn ... nil) (error t)))` which passes on *any* error, not just the expected one.\n\n### Moderate Issues\n- Duplicate test: `ecard-display-test-contact-count-empty` tests same path as `test-contact-count-without-resources`\n- `ecard-widget-test-get-value-no-ecard` uses bare `should-error` without `:type`\n- `ecard-widget-modified-p` test is fragile against serialization changes\n- Inconsistent handling of `ecard-display-contacts-page-size` (some tests use `let`-binding correctly, others use `setq`)\n\n### Minor Issues\n- Unused helper `ecard-widget-test--with-widget-buffer` (dead code)\n- `ecard-display-test-contacts-populate-fallback` swallows all errors making it imprecise\n- No test for multiple address extraction roundtrip in widget tests\n- No test for user declining discard in `ecard-display-contact-quit`\n\n### Strengths\n- Excellent mock server integration tests with proper setup/teardown\n- Thorough error path coverage (parse, validation, generic, conflict errors)\n- Good use of `cl-letf` for mocking interactive functions\n- Strong helper function unit tests with edge cases\n- Full roundtrip and data integrity tests\n- Proper `unwind-protect` cleanup in nearly all tests\n\n### Summary Table\n| Category | display-test | widget-test |\n|----------|-------------|-------------|\n| Critical | 1 | 1 (shared: silent `when` guards) |\n| Moderate | 3 | 2 |\n| Minor | 3 | 3 |\n\nThe highest-priority fix is replacing `when` guards with `should` assertions across both files. This would prevent tests from silently passing when widget lookup fails.\n</teammate-message>",
